owl:Ontology.dc:title: Vocabulario para la representación de datos sobre el tráfico de vehículos a motor de las ciudades.
Vocabulary for the representation of data on traffic made by motor vehicles.
owl:Ontology.terms:creator: Adolfo Antón Bravo (Ontology Engineering Group - Universidad Politécnica de Madrid)
owl:Ontology.rdfs:comment: Esta versión ha sido generada dentro del contexto del proyecto Plataforma de gobierno abierto, colaborativa e interoperable en el que participan los ayuntamientos de Madrid, Zaragoza, Santiago de Compostela y A Coruña. En esta versión se han definido clases y propiedades de acuerdo a los requisitos y glosario de conceptos propuestos en las reuniones del grupo.

This version has been generated within the context of the project Open, collaborative and interoperable government platform in which the city councils of Madrid, Zaragoza, Santiago de Compostela and A Coruña participate. In this version, classes and properties have been defined according to the requirements and glossary of concepts proposed at the group's meetings.
owl:Ontology.owl:versionInfo: Esta es la versión inicial de la ontología de Tráfico que ha sido implementada en el contexto del proyecto Plataforma de gobierno abierto, colaborativa e interoperable en la que participan los ayuntamientos de Madrid, Zaragoza, Santiago de Compostela y A Coruña.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Relación de la Incidencia con el Tramo donde se produce la misma.

Incidencia en tramo

Relationship of the Section with the Track/s it covers, in case the it is indicated
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Tracks
Vía
está en el esquema
is in scheme
owl:ObjectProperty.skos:definition: Relaciona un recurso (por ejemplo un concepto) con un esquema de conceptos en el que está incluido.
Relates a resource (for example a concept) to a concept scheme in which it is included.

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Beginning of a temporal entity
Comienzo de una entidad temporal.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has Beginning
Tiene principio

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: End of a temporal entity
Final de una entidad temporal.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Has End
Tiene final

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: A relation between an Observation and the entity whose quality was observed.
Una relación entre una Observación y la entidad para la que se ha observado.

has feature of interest

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Relación entre una Observación y un Sensor que realiza la Observación.
Relation between an Observation and the Sensor which made the Observation.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: made by sensor
realizada por sensor

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Relación que enlaza la propiedad que se observa.
Relation linking an Observation to the property that was observed. The ObservableProperty should be a property of the FeatureOfInterest (linked by hasFeatureOfInterest) of this Observation.

propiedad observada

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Relación entre un Sensor y una Propiedad Observada que es capaz de obtener observaciones.
Relation between a Sensor and an ObservableProperty that it is capable of sensing.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: Observa
observes

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad establece el intervalo de tiempo de la observación.
This property sets the interval of time of the observation

Intervalo

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Date of creation of the resource.
Fecha de creación del recurso.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Creado

Una descripción del recurso dentro de un contexto dado.

Description

Referencia inequívoca al recurso dentro de un contexto dado.

Identifier

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: La fecha y hora de publicación de una incidencia (en formato fecha ISO 8601)
The end date and time of the incidence (in ISO 8601 date format).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: fecha de publicación de incidencia
posted incidence date

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: La fecha y hora de finalización de una incidencia (en formato fecha ISO 8601)
The end date and time of an incidence (in ISO 8601 date format).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: end date
fecha de fin
(expected) start date
La fecha y hora de inicio de una incidencia (en formato fecha ISO 8601).
The start date and time of an incidence (in ISO 8601 date format).
fecha de inicio (prevista)

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad permite conocer si el dispositivo funciona o no.
This property allows describing whether the device is working or not.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: En Servicio
Running device

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad permite describir si la incidencia es recurrente o no.
This property allows describing whether there is a recurrence in the incidence or not
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Incidencia recurrente
Recurrent incidence

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: La fecha y hora prevista de finalización de una incidencia planificada (en formato fecha ISO 8601)
The end date and time of a planned incidence (in ISO 8601 date format).
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: (expected) end date
fecha de fin (prevista)

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad permite conocer la frecuencia de medición del dispositivo.
This property allows to know the measurement frequency of the device.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Frecuencia Medición
Measurement Frequency

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Number of lanes of traffic
Número de carriles de circulación
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Carriles de circulación
Traffic lanes

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Number of directions of traffic
Número de sentidos de circulación
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Sentidos de circulación
Street directions

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad permite describir la recurrencia.
This property allows describing the recurrence
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Recurrence
Recurrencia

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: En el caso del nivelDeServicio, las medidas posibles son: verde o fluido; amarillo o lento; naranja o denso; rojo o congestión; negro o circulación interrumpida; gris o sin datos.
Esta propiedad permite describir la unidad de medida de la medición del Dispositivo de Medición de Tráfico.
In the case of the Service level, the possible measures are: green or fluid; yellow or slow; orange or dense; red or congestion; black or interrupted circulation; grey or no data.
This property allows describing the unit of measurement of the Trafic Monitoring Device
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Unidad de Medida
Unit of Measurement

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad permite describir si el dispositivo es urbano o no.
This property allows knowing whether the device is urban or not
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Urban
Urbano

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad permite conocer si se ha producido una validación de la observación o no
This property states whether the observation is validated or not.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: Validada
Validated Observation

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad muestra el resultado de la observación.
This property shows the result of the observation

Resultado observación

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Esta propiedad establece la fecha/hora de la observación.
This property sets the dateTime of the observation

Phenomenon Time

X-Coordinate in meters (ETRS89)

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Coordenada Y en metros (ETRS89)
Y-Coordinate in meters (ETRS89)

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Dispositivo de medición de tráfico
Traffic Measuring Device

Un Equipo de Tráfico es uno de los equipos que se encargan de controlar o monitorizar el tráfico de la ciudad.

Traffic equipment

Incidencia que ocurre en el sistema de tráfico de una ciudad

Incidencia

Unplanned traffic incidence
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Incidencia no planificada
Unplanned incidence

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Incidencia planificada, puede ser recurrente o no
Planned traffic incidence
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Incidencia planificada
Planned incidence

Observation by a Traffic Measuring Device

Traffic monitoring

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Property of the Meassurement of Traffic: composition, load, occupation, intensity, level or speed.
Propiedad de la Medición de Tráfico: composición, carga, ocupación, intensidad, nivel o velocidad.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Propiedad Medición Tráfico
Traffic meassuring property

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Section/s of a Track defined by a starting and an ending Point.
Tramo definido por un punto de inicio y fin que puede pertenecer a una o más vías
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Section of Track
Tramo

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Part of street network
Parte del callejero
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Street
Vía

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents the top-level feature type. This class is equivalent to GFI_Feature defined in ISO 19156, and it is superclass of all feature types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Feature

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Esta clase representa el tipo de geometría de alto nivel. Es equivalente a GFI_Geometry definida en ISO 19156 y es superclase de todos los tipos geométricos.
This class represents the top-level geometry type. This class is equivalent to GFI_Geometry defined in ISO 19156, and it is superclass of all geometry types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Geometry
Geometría

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents the top-level spatial object type. This class is equivalent to GFI_SpatialObject defined in ISO 19156, and it is superclass of all spatial object types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SpatialObject

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: This class represents the top-level point type. This class is equivalent to GFI_Point defined in ISO 19156, and it is superclass of all point types.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Point
Concept
owl:Class.skos:definition: An abstract idea or notion; a unit of thought.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A concept scheme may be defined to include concepts from different sources.

Thesauri, classification schemes, subject heading lists, taxonomies, 'folksonomies', and other types of controlled vocabulary are all examples of concept schemes. Concept schemes are also embedded in glossaries and terminologies.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Concept Scheme
owl:Class.skos:definition: A set of concepts, optionally including statements about semantic relationships between those concepts.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with zero extent or duration.
Una entidad temporal con extensión o duración de cero.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Instante de tiempo
Time instant

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with an extent or duration.
Una entidad temporal con extensión o duración
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Time interval
intervalo

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal entity with non-zero extent or duration, i.e. for which the value of the beginning and end are different.
Una entidad temporal con extensión o duración distinta de cero, es decir, para la cual los valores de principio y fin del intervalo son diferentes
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Proper interval
intervalo preciso

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: A temporal interval or instant.
Un intervalo temporal o un instante.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Entidad temporal
Temporal Entity

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The thing whose property is being estimated or calculated in the course of an Observation to arrive at a Result or whose property is being manipulated by an Actuator, or which is being sampled or transformed in an act of Sampling.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Feature Of Interest
owl:Class.skos:definition: The thing whose property is being estimated or calculated in the course of an Observation to arrive at a Result or whose property is being manipulated by an Actuator, or which is being sampled or transformed in an act of Sampling.
owl:Class.skos:example: When measuring the height of a tree, the height is the observed ObservableProperty, 20m may be the Result of the Observation, and the tree is the FeatureOfInterest. A window is a FeatureOfInterest for an automatic window control Actuator.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: An observable quality (property, characteristic) of a FeatureOfInterest.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Observable Property
owl:Class.skos:definition: An observable quality (property, characteristic) of a FeatureOfInterest.
owl:Class.skos:example: The height of a tree, the depth of a water body, or the temperature of a surface are examples of observable properties, while the value of a classic car is not (directly) observable but asserted.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Act of carrying out an (Observation) Procedure to estimate or calculate a value of a property of a FeatureOfInterest. Links to a Sensor to describe what made the Observation and how; links to an ObservableProperty to describe what the result is an estimate of, and to a FeatureOfInterest to detail what that property was associated with
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Observation
owl:Class.skos:definition: Act of carrying out an (Observation) Procedure to estimate or calculate a value of a property of a FeatureOfInterest. Links to a Sensor to describe what made the Observation and how; links to an ObservableProperty to describe what the result is an estimate of, and to a FeatureOfInterest to detail what that property was associated with.
owl:Class.skos:example: The activity of estimating the intensity of an Earthquake using the Mercalli intensity scale is an Observation as is measuring the moment magnitude, i.e., the energy released by said earthquake.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Device, agent (including humans), or software (simulation) involved in, or implementing, a Procedure. Sensors respond to a stimulus, e.g., a change in the environment, or input data composed from the results of prior Observations, and generate a Result. Sensors can be hosted by Platforms.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sensor
owl:Class.skos:definition: Device, agent (including humans), or software (simulation) involved in, or implementing, a Procedure. Sensors respond to a stimulus, e.g., a change in the environment, or input data composed from the results of prior Observations, and generate a Result. Sensors can be hosted by Platforms.
owl:Class.skos:example: Accelerometers, gyroscopes, barometers, magnetometers, and so forth are Sensors that are typically mounted on a modern smart phone (which acts as Platform). Other examples of sensors include the human eyes.

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: It is obtained by the equation of intensity and time of occupation with certain correction factors. It is expressed as a percentage: a 100% load implies circulatory collapse, interrupted circulation, while 0% implies empty street. It is similar to the Level of Service of the road that is usually measured with the letters A, B, C, D, E and F: level A, between 0% and 20% load; level F, between 90% and 100% load. The level of service is complex to measure and that is why the load is used.

Se obtiene mediante ecuación de intensidad y tiempo de ocupación con ciertos factores de corrección. Se expresa en tanto por ciento: una carga del 100% implica colapso circulatorio, circulación interrumpida, mientras que 0% implica calle vacía. Es similar al Nivel de Servicio de la vía que habitualmente se mide con las letras A, B, C, D, E y F: nivel A, entre 0% y 20% de carga; nivel F, entre 90% y 100% de carga. El nivel de servicio es complejo de medir y por eso se usa la carga.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: carga
traffic load

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: It is obtained by the equation of intensity and time of occupation with certain correction factors. It is expressed as a percentage: a 100% load implies circulatory collapse, interrupted circulation, while 0% implies empty street. It is similar to the Level of Service of the road that is usually measured with the letters A, B, C, D, E and F: level A, between 0% and 20% load; level F, between 90% and 100% load. The level of service is complex to measure and that is why the load is used.

Se refiere al tipo de vehículos que se suman en la intensidad y a día de hoy sólo se pueden medir a mano mediante muestreo y calcular coeficientes de corrección para las intensidad. Los vehículos se deben referir a vehículos tipo y estiman valores aproximados: turismo=1 ; motocicleta=0,75; Bicicleta=0,5; Autobús=1,5; Camión grande=2.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: composicion
composition

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Intensidad o aforo, número de vehículos en unidad de tiempo (hora, día, mes año). Los habituales son hora y día.
Intensity or capacity, number of vehicles in time unit (hour, day, month, year). The usual ones are hour and day.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: intensidad
traffic intensity

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Calculado a partir de la velocidad, requiere una ecuación o unos niveles de velocidad asociados: verde, fluido; amarillo, lento; naranja, denso; rojo, congestión; negro, circulación interrumpida; gris, sin datos
Calculated from the speed, it requires an equation or associated speed levels: green, fluid; yellow, slow; orange, dense; red, congestion; black, traffic interrupted; grey, no data.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: level
nivel

owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:comment: Es la ocupación del detector mientras está pasando por encima un vehículo, está asociado a detectores tipo espira electromagnética, y es el tiempo desde que el detector detecta al vehículo hasta que deja detectarlo.

It is the occupation of the detector while it is passing over a vehicle, it is associated with electromagnetic loop type detectors, and it is the time from when the detector detects the vehicle until it allows it to be detected.
owl:NamedIndividual.rdfs:label: occupation
ocupación

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the resource.
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: Date Issued

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Posición de un instante, expresado utilizando xsd:gYearMonth.
Position of an instant, expressed using xsd:gYearMonth
rdf:Description.rdfs:label: en año-mes gregoriano XSD
in XSD g-YearMonth
